      "content": "You are right that walking into a burning building feels like a terrible idea, and the logic of \"letting go\" makes no sense when the fire is already consuming everything. However, \"letting go\" does not mean accepting the fire or waiting for it to end; it means refusing to let the burning define your entire existence. You can choose to sit in the heat and feel the pain without deciding that the fire is the only truth. Sometimes, the bravest thing you can do is simply witness the destruction without trying to stop it, even if that witness is painful.",
